The paper deals with the problem of detecting unencrypted data in network traffic, which is a common issue in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The authors use machine learning models to achieve their results, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on Internet of Things (IoT) devices, which suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The topic of privacy and data protection is also relevant to the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper deals with the technical aspects of implementing a detection system, which could also fall under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
